{
  "text": "Construction of immunoglobulin expression plasmids. The chimeric mousehuman L-chain expression vector was engineered (Fig. 1A) by modifying the human constant module from pING2016E-gpt [CITATION_1] 50) by PCR mutagenesis with primers 5Ј CL (5Ј-CTGCATGATCAGTATCGATCTTCCCGCC-3Ј) and 3Ј CL (5Ј-CCGAGCTCAGGCCCTGATGGG-3Ј) containing ClaI and SacI restriction sites at the 5Ј and 3Ј ends, respectively, creating plasmid pING2016E-gpt*. The ϩ RNA from hybridoma cells secreting MAb 6A.C3 was used as the template for an RT-PCR to obtain the cDNA encoding the VL module. The 5Ј end oligonucleotide corresponding to the RNA leader (L) and the 3Ј end oligonucleotide complementary to the first mouse constant-module nucleotides contained SalI and ClaI restriction endonuclease sites, respectively, to facilitate the cloning of the RT-PCR-derived cDNA into pBluescript SK Ϫ . The ClaI restriction endonuclease site starts at nucleotide 405 of the L-chain gene. The human L-chain (CL) module cloned into the expression vector pING2016E-gpt was modified by PCR to introduce a ClaI restriction site into the 5Ј end. The resulting VL and CL fragments were joined at the ClaI restriction site and cloned into the expression vector pING2016E-gpt* by using the SalI and SacI sites, yielding plasmid pINLC6A. (B) Cloning of the rMH H-chain cDNA. PolyA ϩ RNA from the hybridoma secreting MAb 6A.C3 was used as the template for an RT-PCR to obtain the cDNA encoding the H-chain VH module. The 5Ј end oligonucleotide corresponding to the RNA leader (L) and the 3Ј end oligonucleotide complementary to the first mouse H-chain constant-module nucleotides contained a BamHI and an ApaI site, respectively, to facilitate the cloning of the RT-PCR cDNA into pBluescript SK Ϫ . The ApaI restriction endonuclease site starts at nucleotide 426 of the H-chain gene. The human H-chain constant modules (CH1, CH2, and CH3) included in vector pGMH6 were digested with ApaI-BamHI, and the resulting fragment was ligated with the BamHI-ApaI fragment (containing the V module) into the BamHI restriction site of plasmid pING2003E-neo, yielding pINHC6A. En, SV-40 enhancer; Pr, SV-40 promoter; A n , polyA sequence; pA, SV-40 polyadenylation signal.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "24868799"
